result.execSummary:
All charges against Johnnie George Harper in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Johnnie George Harper is presumed innocent.

For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

judgments.dispoDesc:
*Dismissed without prejudice.
*Reason: The State asserts that the defendant, while in the State of California, signed a document titled Notice and Conditions of Parole. That document contained a waiver of the right to contest extradition back to the State of California. The State also asserts that it was notified
by an individual in the Portage County Jail that an extradition team from the State of California took the defendant into custody and extradited him back to California on June 7, 2022. The State asserts that this matter now lacks prosecutive merit and the defendant is no longer in the State of Wisconsin.
